obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (2832)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2832&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Airports Economic`
  line `Regulatory Authority of India Act, 2008.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line
  line `(3) It applies to--`
  line
  line `(a) all airports whereat air transport services are operated or are intended to be operated, other`
  line `than airports and airfields belonging to or subject to the control of the Armed Forces or paramilitary`
  line `Forces of the Union;`
  line
  line `(b) all private airports and leased airports;`
  line
  line `(c) all civil enclaves;`
  line
  line `(d) all major airports.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st January, 2009 (except Chapters III and IV), vide notification No. S.O. 1894(E), dated 30th December, 2008, see Gazette of`
  line `India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (2833)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2833&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) aeronautical service means any service provided--`
  line
  line `(i) for navigation, surveillance and supportive communication thereto for air traffic`
  line management;
  line
  line `(ii) for the landing, housing or parking of an aircraft or any other ground facility offered in`
  line `connection with aircraft operations at an airport;`
  line
  line `(iii) for ground safety services at an airport;`
  line
  line `(iv) for ground handling services relating to aircraft, passengers and cargo at an airport;`
  line
  line `(v) for the cargo facility at an airport;`
  line
  line `(vi) for supplying fuel to the aircraft at an airport; and`
  line
  line `(vii) for a stake-holder at an airport, for which the charges, in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government for the reasons to be recorded in writing, may be determined by the Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) airport means a landing and taking off area for aircrafts, usually with runways and aircraft`
  line `maintenance and passenger facilities and includes an aerodrome as defined in clause (2) of section 2`
  line `of the Aircraft Act, 1934 (22 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(c) airport user means any person availing of passenger or cargo facilities at an airport;`
  line
  line `^1[(d) Appellate Tribunal means the Airports Economic Regulatory Authority Appellate Tribunal`
  line `established under section 17;]`
  line
  line `(e) Authority means the Airports Economic Regulatory Authority established under sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(f) civil enclave means an area, if any, allotted at an airport belonging to any armed force of the`
  line `Union, for use by persons availing of any air transport services from such airport or for the handling`
  line `of baggage or cargo by such service, and includes land comprising of any building and structure on`
  line `such area;`
  line
  line `(g) Chairperson means the Chairperson of the Authority appointed under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(h) leased airport means an airport in respect of which a lease has been made under section 12A`
  line `of the Airports Authority of India Act, 1994 (55 of 1994);`
  line
  line `(i) major airport means any airport which has, or is designated to have, annual passenger`
  line `throughput in excess of ^2[three and a half million] or any other airport ^3[or a group of airports] as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify as such;`
  line
  line `(j) Member means a Member of the Authority and includes the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(k) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) private airport has the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (nn) of section 2 of the`
  line `Airports Authority of India Act, 1994 (55 of 1994);`
  line
  line `(m) regulations means regulations made by the Authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) service provider means any person who provides aeronautical services and is eligible to levy`
  line `and charge user development fees from the embarking passengers at any airport and includes the`
  line `authority which manages the airport;`
  line
  line `(o) stake-holder includes a licensee of an airport, airlines operating thereat, a person who`
  line `provides aeronautical services, and any association of individuals, which in the opinion of the`
  line `Authority, represents the passenger or cargo facility users;`
  line
  line `(p) words and expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Airports Authority`
  line `of India Act, 1994 (55 of 1994) shall have the same meanings respectively assigned to them in that`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 170, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2019, s. 2, for one and a half million (w.e.f. 26-9-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2021, s. 2 (w.e.f. 13-4-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (2834)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2834&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, within three months from the`
  line `date of commencement of this Act, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish an Authority, to be`
  line `known as the Airports Economic Regulatory Authority, to exercise the powers conferred on, and the`
  line `functions assigned to it, by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Authority shall be at such place as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (2835)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Composition of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2835&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall consist of a Chairperson and two other`
  line `Members to be appointed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that whenever the Authority is deciding a matter involving a civil enclave in a defence`
  line `airfield, there shall be an additional Member, not below the rank of Additional Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India, to be nominated by the Ministry of Defence`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and Members of the Authority shall be appointed by the Central Government`
  line `from amongst persons of ability and integrity having adequate knowledge of, and professional experience`
  line `in, aviation, economics, law, commerce or consumer affairs:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who is or has been in the service of Government shall not be appointed as a`
  line `Member unless such person has held the post of Secretary or Additional Secretary to the Government of`
  line `India or any equivalent post in the Central or State Government for a total period of not less than three`
  line years.
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson and other Members shall be whole-time Members.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson or other Members shall not hold any other office.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson shall be the Chief Executive of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chairperson and other Members of the Authority shall be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government on the recommendation of Selection Committee referred to in section 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (2836)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Constitution of Selection Committee to recommend Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2836&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall, for the purpose of sub-section (6) of section 4 constitute a Selection Committee consisting of the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Cabinet Secretary --Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) Secretary, in the Ministry of Civil Aviation --Member;`
  line
  line `(c) Secretary, Department of Legal Affairs in the Ministry of`
  line
  line `Law and Justice --Member;`
  line
  line `(d) Secretary, in the Ministry of Defence --Member;`
  line
  line `(e) One expert to be nominated by the Ministry of Civil Aviation --Member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall within one month from the date of occurrence of any vacancy by`
  line `reason of death, resignation or removal of the Chairperson or a Member and six months before the`
  line `superannuation or end of tenure of the Chairperson or any Member, make a reference to the Selection`
  line `Committee for filling up of the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(3) The Selection Committee shall finalise the selection of the Chairperson and Members within one`
  line `month from the date on which the reference is made to it.`
  line
  line `(4) The Selection Committee shall recommend a panel of two names for every vacancy referred to it.`
  line
  line `(5) Before recommending any person for appointment as a Chairperson or other Member of the`
  line `Authority, the Selection Committee shall satisfy itself that such person does not have any financial or`
  line `other interest which is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as a Member.`
  line
  line `(6) No appointment of the Chairperson or other Member shall be invalid merely by reason of any`
  line `vacancy in the Selection Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (2837)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Terms of office and other conditions of service, etc., of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2837&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Chairperson and other Members, shall hold office, as such, for a term of five years from the date on which`
  line `he enters upon his office, but shall not be eligible for re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Chairperson or other Member shall hold office, as such, after he attains --`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the Chairperson, the age of sixty-five years; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other Member, the age of sixty-two years.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, a Member may be appointed as Chairperson of`
  line `the Authority, but a person who has been the Chairperson shall not be eligible for appointment as a`
  line Member.
  line
  line `(2) The salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and other Members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The salary, allowances and other conditions of service of the Chairperson and other Members`
  line `shall not be varied to their disadvantage after their appointment.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Chairperson or any Member may,--`
  line
  line `(a) relinquish his office by giving, in writing to the Central Government, a notice of not less than`
  line `three months; or`
  line
  line `(b) be removed from his office in accordance with the provisions of section 8.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson or any Member ceasing to hold office, as such, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be ineligible for further employment under the Central Government or any State Government`
  line `for a period of two years from the date he ceases to hold such office;`
  line
  line `(b) not accept any commercial employment including private for a period of two years from the`
  line `date he ceases to hold such office; or`
  line
  line `(c) not represent any person before the Authority in any other manner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "employment under the Central Government or State Government" includes employment`
  line `under any local or other authority within the territory of India or under the control of the Central`
  line `Government or State Government or under any corporation or society owned or controlled by the`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(b) "commercial employment" means employment in any capacity under, or agency of, a person`
  line `engaged in trading, commercial, industrial or financial business in any field and includes also a`
  line `director of a company or partner of a firm and it also includes setting up practice either independently`
  line `or as partner of a firm or as an adviser or a consultant.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (2838)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2838&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson shall have powers of general superintendence and`
  line `directions in the conduct of the affairs of the Authority and he shall, in addition to presiding over the`
  line `meetings of the Authority, exercise and discharge such powers and functions of the Authority and shall`
  line `discharge such other powers and functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (2839)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Removal and suspension of Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2839&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by order, remove`
  line `from office the Chairperson or other Member, if the Chairperson or such other Member, as the case may`
  line be,--
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a Member; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest, as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `a Member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position, as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line `interest; or`
  line
  line `(f) has engaged at any time during his term of office in any other employment.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or any other Member shall not be removed from his office except by an order of`
  line `the Central Government on the ground of his proved misbehavior or incapacity after the Central`
  line `Government, has, on an inquiry, held in accordance with the procedure prescribed in this behalf by the`
  line `Central Government, come to the conclusion that the Member ought on any such ground to be removed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may suspend any Member in respect of whom an inquiry under`
  line `sub-section (2) is being initiated or pending until the Central Government has passed an order on receipt`
  line `of the report of the inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (2840)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Appointment of Secretary, experts, professionals and officers and other employees of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2840&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may appoint a Secretary to discharge his functions under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) The Authority may appoint such officers and other employees as it considers necessary for the`
  line `efficient discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances payable to and other terms and conditions of service of the Secretary`
  line `and officers and other employees of the Authority and the number of such officers and other employees`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority may engage, in accordance with the procedure specified by regulations such`
  line `number of experts and professionals of integrity and outstanding ability, who have special knowledge of,`
  line `and experience in, economics, law, business or such other disciplines related to aviation as it deems`
  line `necessary to assist the Authority in the discharge of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (2841)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2841&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall meet at such places and times and shall observe such rules of`
  line `procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at its meetings),`
  line `as may be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall preside at the meeting of the Authority and if for any reason the`
  line `Chairperson is unable to attend a meeting of the Authority, any other Member chosen by the members`
  line `present from amongst themselves at the meeting shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Authority shall be decided by a majority`
  line `of votes of the Members present and voting and, in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairperson or`
  line `the Member presiding shall have the right to exercise a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(4) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (1), every Member shall have one vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (2842)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Authentication.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2842&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions of the Authority shall be authenticated by signatures`
  line `of the Secretary or any other officer of the Authority, duly authorised by the Authority in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (2843)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2843&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceedings of the`
  line `Authority shall be invalid merely by reason of --`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in, the constitution of the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a Member of the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Authority not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (2844)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Functions of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2019, s. 3 (w.e.f. 26-9-2019)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2844&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall perform the following functions in respect of`
  line `major airports, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to determine the tariff for the aeronautical services taking into consideration--`
  line
  line `(i) the capital expenditure incurred and timely investment in improvement of airport facilities;`
  line
  line `(ii) the service provided, its quality and other relevant factors;`
  line
  line `(iii) the cost for improving efficiency;`
  line
  line `(iv) economic and viable operation of major airports;`
  line
  line `(v) revenue received from services other than the aeronautical services;`
  line
  line `(vi) the concession offered by the Central Government in any agreement or memorandum of`
  line `understanding or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(vii) any other factor which may be relevant for the purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that different tariff structures may be determined for different airports having`
  line `regard to all or any of the above considerations specified at sub-clauses (i) to (vii);`
  line
  line `(b) to determine the amount of the development fees in respect of major airports;`
  line
  line `(c) to determine the amount of the passengers service fee levied under rule 88 of the Aircraft`
  line `Rules, 1937 made under the Aircraft Act, 1934 (22 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(d) to monitor the set performance standards relating to quality, continuity and reliability of`
  line `service as may be specified by the Central Government or any authority authorised by it in this`
  line behalf;
  line
  line `(e) to call for such information as may be necessary to determine the tariff under clause (a);`
  line
  line `(f) to perform such other functions relating to tariff, as may be entrusted to it by the Central`
  line `Government or as may be necessary to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), the Authority shall not`
  line `determine the tariff or tariff structures or the amount of development fees in respect of an airport or part`
  line `thereof, if such tariff or tariff structures or the amount of development fees has been incorporated in the`
  line `bidding document, which is the basis for award of operatorship of that airport:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall be consulted in advance regarding the tariff, tariff structures or the`
  line `amount of development fees which is proposed to be incorporated in the said bidding document and such`
  line `tariff, tariff structures or the amount of development fees shall be notified in the Official Gazette.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall determine the tariff once in five years and may if so considered appropriate`
  line `and in public interest, amend, from time to time during the said period of five years, the tariff so`
  line determined.
  line
  line `(3) While discharging its functions under sub-section (1) the Authority shall not act against the`
  line `interest of the sovereignty and integrity of India, the security of the State, friendly relations with foreign`
  line `States, public order, decency or morality.`
  line
  line `(4) The Authority shall ensure transparency while exercising its powers and discharging its functions,`
  line `inter alia,--`
  line
  line `(a) by holding due consultations with all stake-holders with the airport;`
  line
  line `(b) by allowing all stake-holders to make their submissions to the authority; and`
  line
  line `(c) by making all decisions of the authority fully documented and explained.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (2845)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Powers of Authority to call for information, conduct investigations, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2845&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `Authority considers it expedient so to do, it may by order in writing--`
  line
  line `(a) call upon any service provider at any time to furnish in writing such information or`
  line `explanation relating to its functions as the Authority may require to access the performance of the`
  line `service provider; or`
  line
  line `(b) appoint one or more persons to make an inquiry in relation to the affairs of any service`
  line `provider; and`
  line
  line `(c) direct any of its officers or employees to inspect the books of account or other documents of`
  line `any service provider.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any inquiry in relation to the affairs of a service provider has been undertaken under subsection`
  line `(1)--`
  line
  line `(a) every office of the Government department, if such service provider is a department of the`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) every director, manager, secretary or other officer, if such service provider is a company; or`
  line
  line `(c) every partner, manager, secretary or other officer, if such service provider is a firm; or`
  line
  line `(d) every other person or body of persons who has had dealings in the course of business with any`
  line `of the persons mentioned in clauses (b) or (c),`
  line
  line `shall be bound to produce before the Authority making the inquiry, all such books of account or other`
  line `documents in his custody or power relating to, or having a bearing on the subject-matter of such inquiry`
  line `and also to furnish to the Authority with any such statement or information relating thereto, as the case`
  line `may be, required of him, within such time as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) Every service provider shall maintain such books of account or other documents as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) The Authority shall have the power to issue such directions to monitor the performance of the`
  line `service providers as it may consider necessary for proper functioning by service providers.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (2846)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of Authority to issue certain directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2846&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may, for the purpose of`
  line `discharge of its functions under this Act, issue, from time to time to the service providers, such directions,`
  line `as it may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (2847)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power of seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2847&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Authority or any other officer specially authorised by it in this behalf`
  line `may enter any building or place where the Authority has reason to believe that any document relating to`
  line `the subject matter of the inquiry may be found, and may seize any such document or take extracts or`
  line `copies therefrom subject to the provisions of section 100 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974) in so far as they may be applicable.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (2848)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Establishment of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2848&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `17. ^1[Appellate Tribunal].-- ^2[The Telecom Disputes Settlement and Appellate Tribunal established`
  line `under section 14 of the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India Act, 1997 (24 of 1997) shall, on and from`
  line `the commencement of Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), be the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal for the purposes of this Act and the said Appellate Tribunal shall exercise the jurisdiction,`
  line `powers and authority conferred on it by or under this Act] to--`
  line
  line `(a) adjudicate any dispute--`
  line
  line `(i) between two or more service providers;`
  line
  line `(ii) between a service provider and a group of consumer:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may, if considers appropriate, obtain the opinion of the`
  line `Authority on any matter relating to such dispute:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this clause shall apply in respect of matters--`
  line
  line `(i) relating to the monopolistic trade practice, restrictive trade practice and unfair trade`
  line `practice which are subject to the jurisdiction of the Monopolies and Restrictive Trade Practices`
  line `Commission established under sub-section (1) of section 5 of the Monopolies and Restrictive`
  line `Trade Practices Act, 1969 (54 of 1969);`
  line
  line `(ii) relating to the complaint of an individual consumer maintainable before a Consumer`
  line `Disputes Redressal Forum or a Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission or the National`
  line `Consumer Redressal Commission established under section 9 of the Consumer Protection Act,`
  line `1986 (68 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(iii) which are within the purview of the Competition Act, 2002 (12 of 2003);`
  line
  line `(iv) relating to an order of eviction which is appealable under section 28K of the Airports`
  line `Authority of India Act, 1994 (55 of 1994).`
  line
  line `(b) hear and dispose of appeal against any direction, decision or order of the Authority under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 170, for "Establishment of Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 170, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (2849)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Application for settlement of disputes and appeals to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2849&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government or a State Government or a local authority or any person may make an application to the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal for adjudication of any dispute as referred to in clause (a) of section 17.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or a State Government or a local authority or any person aggrieved by`
  line `any direction, decision or order made by the Authority may prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under sub-section (2) shall be preferred within a period of thirty days from the date`
  line `on which a copy of the direction or order or decision made by the Authority is received by the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government or the local authority or the aggrieved person and it shall be in such`
  line `form, verified in such manner and be accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain any appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1) or an appeal under sub-section (2)/i@, the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties to the dispute or the appeal an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the parties to the dispute or`
  line `the appeal and to the Authority, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) The application made under sub-section (1) or the appeal preferred under sub-section (2) shall be`
  line `dealt with by it as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the`
  line `application or appeal finally within ninety days from the date of receipt of application or appeal, as the`
  line `case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such application or appeal could not be disposed of within the said period of`
  line `ninety days, the Appellate Tribunal shall record its reasons in writing for not disposing of the application`
  line `or appeal within that period.`
  line
  line `(7) The Appellate Tribunal may, for the purpose of examining the legality or propriety or correctness,`
  line `of any dispute made in any application under sub-section (1), or of any direction or order or decision of`
  line `the Authority referred to in the appeal preferred under sub-section (2), on its own motion or otherwise,`
  line `call for the records relevant to disposing of such application or appeal and make such orders as it thinks`
  line fit.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
