obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (2859)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Civil court not to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2859&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit`
  line `or proceeding in respect of any matter which the Appellate Tribunal is empowered by or under this Act to`
  line `determine and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of any action taken`
  line `or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (2860)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Procedure and powers of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2860&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Tribunal shall not be bound`
  line `by the procedure laid down by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), but shall be guided by the`
  line `principles of natural justice and, subject to the other provisions of this Act, the Appellate Tribunal shall`
  line `have powers to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, the`
  line `same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while`
  line `trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) subject to the provisions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of`
  line `1872), requisitioning any public record or document or a copy of such record or document, from any`
  line office;
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(g) dismissing an application for default or deciding it, ex parte;`
  line
  line `(h) setting aside any order of dismissal of any application for default or any order passed by it,`
  line `ex parte; and`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every proceeding before the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding`
  line `within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860) and the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195`
  line `and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (2861)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Right to legal representation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2861&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The applicant or appellant may either appear in person or`
  line `authorises one or more chartered accountants or company secretaries or cost accountants or legal`
  line `practitioners or any of its officers to present his or its case before the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "chartered accountant" means a chartered accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949) and who has obtained a`
  line `certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "company secretary" means a company secretary as defined in clause (c) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980) and who has obtained a certificate of`
  line `practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "cost accountant" means a cost accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of 1959), and who has obtained a`
  line `certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "legal practitioner" means an advocate, vakil or an attorney of any High Court, and includes a`
  line `pleader in practice.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (2862)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2862&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) or in any other law, an appeal shall lie against any order, not being an`
  line `interlocutory order, of the Appellate Tribunal to the Supreme Court on one or more of the grounds`
  line `specified in section 100 of that Code.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie against any decision or order made by the Appellate Tribunal with the consent`
  line `of the parties.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a period of ninety days from the date of`
  line `the decision or order appealed against:`
  line hr1
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of ninety`
  line `days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the appeal in`
  line time.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (2863)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Orders passed by Appellate Tribunal to be executable as a decree.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2863&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) An order passed by`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal under this Act shall be executable by the Appellate Tribunal as a decree of civil`
  line `court, and for this purpose, the Appellate Tribunal shall have all the powers of a civil court.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal may transmit any`
  line `order made by it to a civil court having local jurisdiction and such civil court shall execute the order as if`
  line `it were a decree made by that court.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (2864)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2864&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The Authority shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial year as`
  line `may be prescribed, its budget for the next financial year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure`
  line `of the Authority and forward the same to the Central Government, for information.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (2865)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2865&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Authority grants of such sums of money as are required`
  line `to be paid for the salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson and other Members and the`
  line `administrative expenses, including the salaries and allowances and pension payable to or in respect of`
  line `officers and other employees of the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (2866)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Annual statement of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2866&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall maintain proper accounts and other`
  line `relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor- General of India`
  line `at such intervals as may be specified by him.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any person appointed by him in connection with`
  line `the audit of the accounts of the Authority under this Act shall have the same rights, privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit, as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India generally has, in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Authority, as certified by Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon, shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and the Central Government shall cause the same to be laid before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (2867)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Furnishing of returns, etc., to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2867&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall furnish to the`
  line `Central Government, at such time and in such form and manner as may be prescribed or as the Central`
  line `Government may direct, such returns and statements and such particulars in regard to any matter under`
  line `the jurisdiction of the Authority, as the Central Government may, from time to time, require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall prepare, once every year, in such form and at such time as may be prescribed,`
  line `an annual report, giving a summary of its activities during the previous year and copies of the report shall`
  line `be forwarded to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the report received under sub-section (2) shall be laid by the Central Government, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (2868)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Penalty for wilful failure to comply with orders of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2868&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `If any person`
  line `wilfully fails to comply with the order of the Appellate Tribunal, he shall be punishable with fine which`
  line `may extend to one lakh rupees and in case of a second or subsequent offence with fine which may extend`
  line `to two lakh rupees and in the case of continuing contravention with additional fine which may extend to`
  line `two lakh rupees for every day during which such default continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (2869)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Punishment for non-compliance of orders and directions under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2869&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fails to`
  line `comply with any order or direction given under this Act, or contravenes, or attempts to contravene or`
  line `abets the contravention of the provisions of this Act or of any rules or regulations made thereunder shall`
  line `be punishable with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees and in the case of a second or subsequent`
  line `offence with fine which may extend to two lakh rupees and in the case of a continuing contravention with`
  line `an additional fine which may extend to four thousand rupees for every day during which the default`
  line continues.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (2870)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Punishment for non-compliance with order of Authority or Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2870&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `If any`
  line `person wilfully fails to comply with an order of the Authority or of the Appellate Tribunal, passed under`
  line `Chapter IV, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees and, in the case of a`
  line `second or subsequent offence, with fine which may extend to two lakh rupees and in the case of a`
  line `continuing failure, with an additional fine which may extend to four thousand rupees for every day during`
  line `which such failure continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (2871)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2871&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to the company for the conduct of, the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company, and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" means a whole-time director in the company and in relation to a firm, means a`
  line `partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (2872)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Offences by Government Departments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2872&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by any Department of Government or any of its undertakings, the Head of the Department or`
  line `its undertakings shall be deemed to be guilty of an offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly unless he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he`
  line `had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by any Department of Government or its undertakings and it is proved that the offence has`
  line `been committed with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any`
  line `officer, other than the Head of the Department, or its undertakings, such officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (2873)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2873&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, from time to time,`
  line `issue to the Authority such directions as it may think necessary in the interest of the sovereignty and`
  line `integrity of India, the security of the State, friendly relations with foreign States, public order, decency or`
  line morality.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions, the Authority shall, in exercise of its powers or the`
  line `performance of its functions, be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central`
  line `Government may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (2874)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Members, officers and employees of Authority to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2874&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson,`
  line `Members, officers and other employees of the Authority shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to`
  line `act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section`
  line `21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (2875)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2875&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any matter which the`
  line `Authority is empowered by or under this Act to determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (2876)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2876&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or the Authority or any Member, officer or other employees thereof`
  line `for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules and regulations`
  line `made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (2877)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Exemption from tax on wealth and income.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2877&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957), the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), or any other enactment for the`
  line `time being in force relating to tax on wealth, income, profits or gains, the Authority shall not be liable to`
  line `pay wealth-tax, income-tax or any other tax in respect of their wealth, income, profits or gains derived.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (2878)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2878&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this`
  line `Act, except upon a complaint in writing made by the Authority or by any officer of the Authority duly`
  line `authorised by the Authority for this purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (2879)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2879&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `The Authority may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to`
  line `the Chairperson or any Member or officer of the Authority, subject to such conditions and limitations, if`
  line `any, as may be specified in the order, such of its powers and functions under this Act (except the power to`
  line `settle disputes and the power to make regulations), as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (2880)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2880&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, at any time, the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that on account of a grave emergency, the Authority is unable to discharge the functions and`
  line `duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the Authority has persistently made default in complying with any direction issued by the`
  line `Central Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions and duties imposed on it by or`
  line `under the provisions of this Act and as a result of which default, the financial position of the`
  line `Authority or the administration of any airport, heliport, airstrip, civil enclave or aeronautical`
  line `communication station has deteriorated; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do, the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, supersede the Authority for such period, not`
  line `exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing a notification under this sub-section for the reasons mentioned in clause`
  line `(b), the Central Government shall give a reasonable opportunity to the Authority to show cause as to why`
  line `it should not be superseded and shall consider the explanations and objections, if any, of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Authority,--`
  line
  line `(a) all the Members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Authority, shall until the Authority is re-constituted under sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by such person or persons as the Central`
  line `Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) all property owned or controlled by the Authority shall, until the Authority is re-constituted`
  line `under sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under subsection`
  line `(1), the Central Government may,--`
  line
  line `(a) extend the period of supersession for such further term not exceeding six months, as it may`
  line `consider necessary; or`
  line
  line `(b) re-constitute the Authority by fresh appointment and in such case the Members who vacated`
  line `their offices under clause (a) of sub-section (2) shall not be deemed disqualified for appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, at any time before the expiration of the period of`
  line `supersession, whether as originally specified under sub-section (1) or as extended under this sub-section,`
  line `take action under clause (b) of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a notification issued under sub-section (1) and a full report of`
  line `any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be laid before both`
  line `Houses of Parliament at the earliest opportunity.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (2881)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2881&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (2882)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Clauses (i), (j) and (k) omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 170 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2882&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the salary and allowances payable to, and the other conditions of service of, the Chairperson`
  line `and other Members under sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner in which and the Authority before whom the oath of office and secrecy`
  line `shall be made and subscribed under sub-section (4) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers and functions to be exercised or discharged by the Chairperson under section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure for conducting any inquiry made under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(e) the salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Secretary, officers and other employees of the Authority under sub-section (3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(f) the performance standards relating to the quality, continuity and reliability of service to be`
  line `monitored under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(g) the books of account or other documents which are required to be maintained by the service`
  line `provider under sub-section (3) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(h) the form and manner in which the form shall be verified and fee to be accompanied by the`
  line `form under sub-section (3) of section 18;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(l) the form in which the Authority shall prepare, and at such time in each financial year, its`
  line `budget and the time at which such budget shall be prepared under section 33;`
  line
  line `(m) the form in which proper accounts and other relevant records shall be maintained and the`
  line `annual statement of accounts shall be prepared by the Authority under sub-section (1) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(n) the form, manner and the time in which the returns and statements shall be furnished by the`
  line `Authority under sub-section (1) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(o) the form and time at which the annual report shall be prepared by the Authority under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (2883)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2883&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `and with the previous approval of the Central Government, make regulations, not inconsistent with this`
  line `Act, and the rules made thereunder, to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure in accordance with which the experts and professionals may be engaged under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(b) the places and time of meetings of the Authority and the procedure to be followed at such`
  line `meetings, (including the quorum at its meetings) under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (2884)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2884&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Central`
  line `Government, and every regulation made by the Authority, under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days,`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should`
  line `not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (2885)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Amendment of certain enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2885&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `The enactments specified in the Schedule to this Act shall`
  line `be amended in the manner specified therein and such amendments shall take effect on the date of`
  line `establishment of the Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (2886)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369&sectionId=2886&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_36_56_00009_200827_1517807327369
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
